# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NJ Park Site Finder — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in values. EVERYTHING here is optional —
# the app runs fine with no variables set (natural-language search and the
# health-check alerts simply stay off). Weather needs no configuration:
# Open-Meteo is keyless.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Natural-language search (the ✨ Ask bar). Get a free key at https://build.nvidia.com
# Server-side only — never sent to the browser.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=

# Optional overrides for the NL model endpoint (defaults shown):
# NVIDIA_BASE_URL=https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1
# NVIDIA_MODEL=nvidia/nemotron-3-ultra-550b-a55b

# Daily scraper health check (netlify/functions/healthcheck.mjs):
# a Slack-compatible incoming webhook that gets pinged when the njportal.com
# scraper breaks. Leave unset to only log failures in the Netlify function logs.
# HEALTHCHECK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...

# For Netlify deploys: set NVIDIA_API_KEY (and optionally HEALTHCHECK_WEBHOOK_URL)
# in Site configuration → Environment variables — do NOT commit your real `.env`
# (it's already in .gitignore).
